      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "\"Sheriff, these disturbances are nothing more than a few agitators stirring up trouble where there was none,\" the business owner might sneer. The judge would nod slowly, his voice dripping with false concern, \"We must maintain order, gentlemen; the peace of this town depends on keeping things as they ought to be.\" The sheriff would agree gruffly, \"Some folks just don't know their place, and we'll have to remind 'em where that is.\" They'd all agree that the problem wasn't the situation, but the people causing it.",
